[section:has_first_reference `has_first_reference`]

[section Synopsis]
[reference__has_first_reference]
[endsect]

[section Description]
This metafunction evaluates to __mpl_true__ if the specified type is
non-`const` and defined with a nested `first_reference` type definition that
is not `void`, or if the specified type is `const`-qualified and defined with
a nested `first_const_reference` type definition that is not `void`.  This
metafunction evaluates to __mpl_false__ otherwise.
[endsect]

[section:definition Where defined]
``
#include <__has_first_reference__header__>
``

--or--

``
